items.title: Module not found in Node.js
items.body_markdown:
Here is a solution to resolve the 'module not found' error in Node.js:

1. Make sure you have installed all the required dependencies for your project.
2. Check if the module is correctly installed by running 'npm ls <module_name>'.
3. If the module is missing, install it using 'npm install <module_name>'.
4. Verify that the module is correctly referenced in your code.
5. Restart your Node.js application and check if the error is resolved.

Hope this helps!
